    "narrative_summary": "The BRCA1 missense variant R1203Q (arginine to glutamine at codon 1203) is noted in the literature as a substitution occurring at a site that has undergone rapid evolution in primates, but the provided evidence does not link it to any specific disease phenotype. The only mention of R1203Q comes from a comparative evolutionary study that identified the residue among several sites showing signatures of positive selection across humans, chimpanzees, bonobos and other primates; the authors did not provide a clinical classification, functional assay result, or population frequency for this change, and no computational pathogenicity prediction was reported [PMC4106182]. In the absence of clinical, functional, or population data, and given that the cited work frames the variant solely in an evolutionary context without asserting pathogenicity, the current evidence does not support a definitive interpretation of R1203Q as disease\u2011causing. Consequently, the variant remains of uncertain significance pending further investigation.",
